$ Oracle hint: DRIVING_SITE
@ driving_site

`driving_site` specifies the «location» where a distributed query is executed. This hint is on → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/hints#ora-hint-jl-big-5[Jonathan Lewis' list of the Big Five Hints]

`driving_site` is not intended (and not «working») for DML or DDL statements, see MOS Noe 825677.1

sa:

  → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/link

  Other → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/hints[hints]
